claims:
Claims 1. Method for gassing and/or degassing a package including a packaging film enclosing an inner space holding a product and a port device connected to the packaging film along a circumferential sealing contour, the port device having an opening within the contour for allowing gas to enter or leave the inner space and a sealing surface surrounding the opening, the port device further having a lid arranged for sealingly abutting against the sealing surface for closing the opening, the lid being selectively moveable from a first position to a second position, wherein in the first position the lid is offset relative to the sealing surface so as to allow gas to enter or leave the inner space, and wherein in the second position the lid sealingly abuts against the sealing surface for closing the opening; the method including: sealingly abutting a suction device against an outer side of the package, at a location of the port device, the suction device having a first connection for being in fluid communication with the opening for degassing the inner space and a second connection for being in fluid communication with the lid; operating the second connection of the suction device for moving the lid to the first position; - with the lid in the first position operating the first connection of the suction device for gassing and/or degassing the inner space; and closing the opening by operating the second connection of the suction device so as to move the lid into the second position. 2. Method according to claim 1, further including, filling the package with an inert gas. 3. Method according to claim 1 or 2, further including, after closing of the opening, re-opening the opening for measuring a pressure and/or gas content of the inner space. 4. Packaging system including a package including: a package including a packaging film enclosing an inner space for holding a product and a suction device for removing gas from the inner space and/or providing gas to the inner space; the packaging system further including: - an element connected to the packaging film along a circumferential sealing contour, the element having an opening within the contour for allowing gas to enter or leave the inner space, the element further having a sealing surface surrounding the opening; and a hd arranged for sealingly abutting against the sealing surface for closing the opening; the system including: an actuator for selectively moving the hd from a first to a second position, wherein in the first position the hd is offset relative to the sealing surface so as to allow gas to enter or leave the inner space, and wherein in the second position the lid sealingly abuts against the sealing surface for closing the opening; wherein the actuator is arranged for drawing the hd towards the first position by means of underpressure; wherein the suction device has a first connection for being in fluid communication with the opening for gassing and/or degassing the inner space and a second connection for being in fluid communication with the actuator. 5 System according to claim 4, wherein the actuator is part of the package. 6. System according to claim 4, wherein the actuator is part of the suction device. 7. System according to any one of claims 4-6, wherein the actuator includes a biasing element for biasing the lid towards the second position. 8. System according to any one of claims 4-7, wherein the package further includes a valve for allowing sampling of a gaseous content of the packaging after closing of the opening. 9. System according to claim 8, wherein the valve is part of the lid. 10. System according to claim 9, wherein the suction device includes a valve deactivator for deactivating the valve while the lid is in the first position. 11. System according to any one of claims 4-10, wherein the suction device includes an inner suction device and an outer suction device, the inner suction device bearing against the element, the outer suction device not bearing against the element. 12. Package including: a packaging film enclosing an inner space for holding a product; - a port device connected to the packaging film along a circumferential sealing contour, the port device having an opening within the contour for allowing gas to enter or leave the inner space, the port device further having a sealing surface surrounding the opening; and a lid arranged for sealingly abutting against the sealing surface for closing the opening; 

 the port device including a first port for being in fluid communication with a first vacuum line for gassing and/or degassing the inner space and a second port for being in fluid communication with a second vacuum line for moving the lid. 13. Package according to claim 12, wherein the lid is arranged to be moved from a first position to a second position, wherein in the first position the lid is offset relative to the sealing surface so as to allow gas to enter or leave the inner space, and wherein in the second position the lid sealingly abuts against the sealing surface for closing the opening. 14. Package according to claim 12 or 13, wherein the package further includes a valve for allowing sampling of a gaseous content of the packaging after closing of the opening. 15. Port device for being connected to a packaging film along a circumferential sealing contour, including: an opening within the contour for allowing gas to pass through the port device, the port device further having a seahng surface surrounding the opening; and a lid arranged for sealingly abutting against the seahng surface for closing the opening; and a first port for being in fluid communication with a first gas line for passing gas through opening and a second port for being in fluid communication with a second vacuum line for moving the lid. 16. Port device according to claim 15, wherein the lid is arranged to be moved from a first position to a second position, wherein in the first position the lid is offset relative to the sealing surface for allowing gas to 

 pass through the opening, and wherein in the second position the lid sealingly abuts against the sealing surface for closing the opening. 17. Port device according to claim 15 or 16, wherein the lid includes a valve for allowing sampling of a gaseous content across the lid. 18. A port device (1), comprising: a port housing with an interior space, the housing having at least one content opening (4) communicating the interior space to the outside; at least one gas exchange opening (44) communicating the interior space to the outside at least one actuator opening (46) communicating the interior space to the outside; - a gas flow path extending between the content opening (4) and the gas exchange opening (44) for fluid flow between the content opening (4) and the gas exchange opening (44) in either direction; at least one lid (8) arranged within the interior space; a first sealing element (6) arranged within the interior space and surrounding the content opening (4); a second sealing element (10) arranged within the interior space and surrounding the actuator opening (46), the second sealing element (10) sealingly engaging the housing and sealingly engaging the lid (8), the second sealing element (10) being effective to prevent fluid flow between the actuator opening (46) and the content opening (4) and being effective to prevent fluid flow between the actuator opening (46) and the gas exchange opening (44); wherein the lid (8) is displaceable between a closed position and a released position, wherein in the closed position the lid (8) sealingly engages the first sealing element (6) to effectively close the gas flow path, and 

 wherein in the released position the lid (8) is free from the first sealing element (6) to allow fluid flow in the gas flow path; wherein the port device further comprises bias means (10) for biasing the lid (8) towards the closed position. 19. A package including a packaging film enclosing a content space for holding a content product; the packaging film having an opening provided with the port device of claim 1, with the content opening (4) communicating with the content space, and the gas exchange opening (44) and actuator opening (46) communicating to the outside of the packaging film. 20. Method for degassing a package according to claim 19, the method comprising the steps of: a) connecting an actuator suction device to the actuator opening (46) and connecting a gas suction device to the gas exchange opening (44); b) operating the actuator suction device to increase underpressure to move the lid (8) to the released position; c) operating the gas suction device for degassing the package content space; d) operating the actuator suction device to reduce underpressure to move the lid (8) to the closed position. 21. Method according to claim 20, further including the steps of: e) disconnecting the gas suction device from the gas exchange opening (44); f) connecting a gas supply device to the gas exchange opening (44); g) operating the actuator suction device to increase underpressure to move the lid (8) to the released position; 

 h) operating the gas supply device for filling the package with an inert gas; i) operating the actuator suction device to reduce underpressure to move the lid (8) to the closed position. 22. Method according to claim 20, further including after step d) the steps of: j) disconnecting the gas suction device from the gas exchange opening (44); k) connecting a gas sampling device and/or a gas pressure measuring device to the gas exchange opening (44); 1) operating the actuator suction device to increase underpressure to move the lid (8) to the released position; m) operating the gas sampling device and/or a gas pressure measuring device for measuring a pressure and/or gas content of the package content space; n) operating the actuator suction device to reduce underpressure to move the lid (8) to the closed position. 23. Method according to claim 21, further including after step i) the steps of: j) disconnecting the gas supply device from the gas exchange opening (44); k) connecting a gas sampling device and/or a gas pressure measuring device to the gas exchange opening (44); 1) operating the actuator suction device to increase underpressure to move the lid (8) to the released position; m) operating the gas sampling device and/or a gas pressure measuring device for measuring a pressure and/or gas content of the package content space; 

 operating the actuator suction device to reduce underpressure to the hd (8) to the closed position.
